  schema:name "Single-Loop and Double-Loop Learning" ;
  schema:description "Single-loop learning corrects errors within a fixed frame. Double-loop learning questions the frame itself. The distinction comes from Chris Argyris and Donald Schön's work on organizational learning [@argyris1978]." ;
